== Wedges ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no 
need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, 
season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single 
layer. 

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. 
Turn halfway through.

== Preparation ==

Meanwhile, finely chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all). Halve, peel and 
thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. 
Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then separate the leaves. Keep 2 
large leaves per person, then thinly slice the rest widthways. Peel and grate 
the @garlic clove{1}(grated, or use a garlic press). Grate the 
@Monterey Jack cheese{30%g}.

== Burger Patties ==

Put the @Mexican style spice mix{1}, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g} and 
@water{2%tbsp} into a large #bowl{}, then mix to combine. Add the 
@British beef mince{240%g}, coriander and garlic. Season with @salt{} and 
@pepper{} then mix together with your hands. Roll the mince into even-sized 
balls, then flatten to make burger patties 1cm thick (1 per person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

== Shallot Relish ==

Pop the burgers onto a lightly oiled baking tray and bake on the middle shelf 
of your oven until cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a small #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the 
shallot and cook until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir occasionally. Transfer 
to a small bowl and stir in the @red pepper chilli jelly{25%g} to make the 
relish.

== Assembly ==

When the burgers are cooked, remove from the oven. Carefully place the cheese 
on top of the burgers. Cover loosely with #foil{} then set aside for 
~{3-4%minutes} for the cheese to melt.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

In another bowl, add the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @olive oil{}. Season, then 
add the sliced lettuce and baby plum tomatoes. Toss to coat.

When everything is ready, stack 2 of the whole baby gem leaves onto each 
serving plate. Pop the cheesy burger on top of the leaves, then top with 
the shallot relish. Serve with the wedges and baby gem salad on the side. 
Enjoy!